parameters:
\PartyFace[1]\FaceIndex[10]I can faintly sense some spiritual power... Could it be the
kidnapped children...?

Wait, before we rescue them, we need to find an escape route
to ensure we can get them out safely!
\PartyFace[1]\FaceIndex[4]Securing a safe escape route should be our priority.

\PartyFace[1]\FaceIndex[10]I can faintly sense some spiritual power... Could it be the
kidnapped children...?

Wait, we need to find an escape route first and make sure we
can get them out safely before we rescue them!
\PartyFace[1]\FaceIndex[4]Securing a safe escape route should be our priority, huh?
It seems there are no traps in this area.

I'd like you to try starting up the VR system first. It's
super convenient!

I'll analyze it, so bring the \C[2]Seraphic Breath\C[0]
close to the electronic lock.

For now, if it's a simple electronic lock, we can unlock it
remotely with the \C[2]Seraphic Breath\C[0], but there might
be some that are too complex to open.

\PartyFace[1](I think we could just break the complex ones, but I'd
probably get scolded, so I'll keep quiet about that.)

I think it's better to have a base for our investigation, so
first let's look for the terminal that manages the
containment facility.

\c[2]If the Liberators \c[0]are involved, we might be dealing
with a rather large organization, so please move with utmost
caution.

"...This door is a bit troublesome, can you give me a little
time?"

Even so... the fact that I sensed divine power from the
captured girls means there's a high chance they're targeting
such children for kidnapping.

It does seem likely that the \c[2]Liberators\C[0] are
involved then.
Hey, that guy's come out again!
What the hell is going on...

Don't make us go through all this trouble! Just go back to
your room already!
Hey, the one we brought in earlier is coming out!?

It's an auto-locking electronic lock, right? It shouldn't
open without an ID...
\PartyFace[1]\FaceIndex[3]\PartyFace[1]Looks like I've been found already, huh?

Seems like we were being monitored here... can't be
helped...
\PartyFace[1]\FaceIndex[9]So it's okay to go ahead and do it?

\PartyFace[1]\FaceIndex[9]With Hisana-chan's permission, I'll have to force my way
through here!
Hah hah hah. Quite the spirited young lady.

Your little stroll ends here. Now, shall we head back to
your room?
No way, is she one of the \C[2]Guardians\C[0]' witches!?
\PartyFace[1]\FaceIndex[10]\c[2]I'd prefer if you called me a magical girl.

...Having \c[2]anti-magical girl equipment\c[0], it's almost
certain that the \c[2]Liberators\c[0] are involved.
\PartyFace[1]\FaceIndex[4]We'll have to move carefully from here on out!

Anyway, since we were being monitored, there must be a
surveillance system nearby. Can you get close to it?
...Yeah, that seems right. Let me try accessing it.

...I see, if you get out of the \c[2]underground containment
facility\c[0] where you are now and make it to the
\c[2]surface research lab\c[0], you might be able to get
outside.
\PartyFace[1]\FaceIndex[0]Got it! Then first, I'll aim for the research lab!
Before that, let me do this with the terminal... and...

I've installed a dummy system in this terminal to disconnect
it from the external surveillance system.
Now we can use this terminal freely.

(She doesn't seem to get it...) Anyway, I've installed a
\c[2]VR system\c[0], so why don't you boot it up?

Seriously... You've made me go through unnecessary trouble!
Make sure you behave this time!
\PartyFace[1]\FaceIndex[4]I won't lose next time, for sure!
Stay put in here quietly, alright?

You won't be able to escape from here anyway, don't waste
your energy before the inspection!

You're too relaxed... Do you even understand the situation
you're in?

\PartyFace[1]\FaceIndex[0]I understand perfectly. You guys are the serial girl
kidnappers that have been causing a stir lately, right?

Oh, well... It bothers me that you're so composed even
though you understand, but... whatever, just wait here for a
while!

...Ah, you finally responded! I've been trying to reach you
forever, what happened!?

\PartyFace[1]\FaceIndex[1]Sorry, sorry, I got kidnapped for a bitsorry to worry you,
\C[2]Hisana\C[0]-chan.
Geez, as long as you're safe... but

\PartyFace[1]\FaceIndex[8]Well, you know, with all the recent cases of girls
disappearing, I thought maybe it had something to do with
the \C[2]Liberators\C[0], and just as I was thinking about
it, someone conveniently tried to kidnap me...
So you got caught on purpose...?

Sigh... Kohane-chan really doesn't think ahead and just
rushes into things... Even though we're \C[2]cousins\C[0], I
can't keep up with that side of you...

\PartyFace[1]\FaceIndex[0]That's where you come in... Hisana-chan, you've got my back,
and I'm counting on you.
Ugh... fine, can't be helped. So, what's the situation?

I see, you're locked up. If we knew where you are, we could
send help...

The location data is... no good, can't get it. Seems like
there's some kind of interference.

\PartyFace[1]\FaceIndex[0]But since we can communicate through \C[2]Seraphic
Breath\C[0] like this, it seems that \C[2]spiritual
power\C[0] is reaching me.

So they're interfering with it and didn't need to take away
your communication device...

Which means... if Kohane-chan can release a large amount of
spiritual power in some open area, we might be able to
pinpoint your location.

\PartyFace[1]\FaceIndex[1]Got it, so I just need to get out of here and go wild,
right?

No way!! There are other kids captured too, so you have to
act carefully until help arrives!

For now, get out of there and look for a \C[2]wide open
space outside the building\C[0] where you can release your
\C[2]spiritual power\C[0].

\PartyFace[1]\FaceIndex[0]Right, I can't beat up the kidnappers unless I get out of
here.

Do you really understand...? It might be pointless to say
this, but please don't do anything reckless since you're
alone...

Then I'll support you remotely, can you go in front of the
door?
\PartyFace[1]\FaceIndex[2]VR system... is this how it works?

For now, it seems best to make this place our base for
exploration.

If things get dangerous, choose the special action to return
to base and come back here.

...My apologies for the late introduction. My name is
\C[2]Yuri Orlov\C[0]. Please remember me.

\PartyFace[1]\FaceIndex[2]Oh, hello, I'm Amagawa Kohane. I'm the magical girl
Seraphier.

I've heard rumors about you. The rising star of the
Guardians, they say...

If you don't mind, would you like to take a look at the
products I offer? I'm sure they will be of use to you.

...Yuri Orlov... I've heard of him. A mysterious merchant
who appears out of nowhere and sells equipment to the
Guardians...
\PartyFace[1]\FaceIndex[2]Huh... So he's like a supporter for the Guardians?

The thing is... no one knows his true identity... but they
say all his goods are top-notch...

Oh... that communication device... It seems to be uniquely
modified, but the base is our product. Thank you for your
continued patronage.
\PartyFace[1]\FaceIndex[2]Wow... really? He must be an amazing person...

\PartyFace[1]\FaceIndex[11]Wait a minute! How did you get here? And where did all the
people we defeated go?

That is a corporate secret... However, I took care of the
fallen guards as a service.
\PartyFace[1]\FaceIndex[8]Took care of them? Where on earth did you put them?
There are things better left unknown.
\PartyFace[1]\FaceIndex[8]...It seems better not to dig too deep into this.
Shall we proceed with the business discussion then?

\PartyFace[1]\FaceIndex[2]Even if you say business discussion, I don't have any money
on me right now?

No problem. My products can be exchanged for \C[2]Guardians
Points\C[0].

They are evaluation points that accumulate based on your
achievements. My shop supports payments with those points
under a contract with the Guardians.
\PartyFace[1]\FaceIndex[1]Eh? So if I do well, I can exchange lots of products?

...Kohane-chan... Guardians Points are our performance
evaluation points, so if you use too many, I think our
rewards from the Guardians might decrease...

\PartyFace[1]\FaceIndex[11]Seriously?! So in the end, it's like paying out of my own
pocket!

\PartyFace[1]\FaceIndex[4]Mmm... I don't want my rewards to decrease, but... desperate
times call for desperate measures...

Whenever you decide whether to use our services or not,
please feel free to call on me.
Welcome. These are the products we currently have available.

Oh my, aren't you cold dressed like that? I recommend using
our products to restore your spiritual power and regenerate
your robe.

...I must say, wandering around dressed like that is
questionable. You should regenerate your robe quickly.

Oh, what a lovely outfit. Is that the kind of play you
prefer?
We look forward to serving you again.
